abstract: Court-ordered desegregation worked. But white racism made it hard to accept.
snippet: Court-ordered desegregation worked. But white racism made it hard to accept.
lead_paragraph: When Senator Kamala Harris confronted former Vice President Joe Biden at the second Democratic presidential debate about his support of bills to ban busing for school desegregation during the 1970s and early ’80s, he gave a sort of denial. “I did not oppose busing in America,” he said. “What I opposed is busing ordered by the Department of Education. That’s what I opposed.”

abstract: Bernie Sanders’s advisers and allies want him to get personal with voters as he struggles in the 2020 race. But that isn’t his style.
snippet: Bernie Sanders’s advisers and allies want him to get personal with voters as he struggles in the 2020 race. But that isn’t his style.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When Senator Bernie Sanders brought his presidential campaign to Pittsburgh earlier this year, he quietly added a poignant stop to his schedule: a visit to the Tree of Life synagogue, where 11 congregants were killed in an anti-Semitic shooting last fall.

snippet: Federal lawyers previously advised the commission to block the company, Area 1, from providing services to presidential candidates at a discount.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The Federal Election Commission said on Thursday that a Silicon Valley security company could immediately start helping 2020 presidential candidates defend their campaigns from the kinds of malicious email attacks that Russian hackers exploited in the 2016 election.

abstract: A study of the Democratic presidential contenders says Gillibrand, Warren and O’Rourke have done the most to help build the party by boosting state legislative candidates.
snippet: A study of the Democratic presidential contenders says Gillibrand, Warren and O’Rourke have done the most to help build the party by boosting state legislative candidates.
lead_paragraph: Amid the relentless focus on Washington and presidential politics, a liberal political action committee has ranked the 2020 Democratic presidential candidates on something much lower on the political food chain — what they are doing to help Democrats win state legislative seats.

lead_paragraph: I am pointedly trying not to make predictions about the presidential race. But I think I can say with confidence that Tom Steyer — a hedge fund billionaire who announced this week that he, too, was running for president — will not be the Democratic nominee.

abstract: The address in New York City took aim at President Trump’s judgment in foreign affairs while also trying to lift Mr. Biden above the Democratic primary fray.
snippet: The address in New York City took aim at President Trump’s judgment in foreign affairs while also trying to lift Mr. Biden above the Democratic primary fray.
lead_paragraph: After spending two weeks sparring with his presidential primary opponents, Joseph R. Biden Jr. sought once more to rise above the Democratic fray on Thursday, delivering a sweeping foreign policy address that denounced President Trump as incapable of global leadership and called for a new commitment to multilateral diplomacy.

abstract: The gathering, which was dominated by activists willing to share unverified smears against Democrats and create memes the president might share, featured melee in the Rose Garden.
snippet: The gathering, which was dominated by activists willing to share unverified smears against Democrats and create memes the president might share, featured melee in the Rose Garden.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As he opened an event that had brought 200 conservative social media firebrands to the White House, President Trump wanted his guests to know just how much he appreciated their work helping shape the online narrative about his presidency and a re-election fight.

abstract: Moises Velasquez-Manoff responds to people from the state who commented on the contradictory nature of race relations there.
snippet: Moises Velasquez-Manoff responds to people from the state who commented on the contradictory nature of race relations there.
lead_paragraph: In my essay “Want to Be Less Racist? Move to Hawaii,” I explore why race might be perceived differently in Hawaii from how it is on the mainland United States. The article grew out of my interest in the psychologist Kristin Pauker’s research, which suggests that kids in Hawaii see race as something much more fluid than kids on the mainland do and that this fluidity can rub off on people from the mainland who enroll in college there.
